<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVE TRAIN - Installation - Fuel Injectors
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26504.4.11" graphiccount="9">
        <title>Fuel Injectors</title>
        <svcsubproc id="s26504.4.11.1">
            <title>Replace Copper Gasket and O-rings for Fuel Injector</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not use air tools when installing fuel injectors. Do not scratch
                        injector surfaces.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, replace external O-rings and copper gasket each time a fuel injector
                        is removed.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the old copper gasket with a small hand tool. Wipe injector nozzle with a lint
                    free cloth.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new copper gasket injector onto injector tip.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>The copper gasket may be installed in either direction.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="f2650494" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd11/d1155.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Seating copper gasket</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Injector (nozzle end)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket (copper)</callout1>
                        <callout1 type="arabic">Deep socket</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To seat gasket, push on gasket with a deep socket.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a nonmetallic hand tool to remove upper and lower O-rings from fuel injector.
                    Discard O-rings.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new Teflon coated (white) O-ring (smaller diameter) in the lower recess just
                    below the fuel screens. Avoid contact with sharp machined surfaces.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650495" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd11/d1111.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Fuel injector external O-rings</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring, lower (white Teflon coating) (smaller diameter)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel inlet screen (3)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring, upper (black Teflon coating) (larger diameter)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Clamp alignment slot</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring, harness connector (dark blue)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install a new Teflon coated (black) O-ring (larger diameter) in the recess just above
                    the fuel inlet screens. Avoid contact with sharp machined surfaces.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650496" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd08/d0893.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Lubrication of fuel injector O-rings</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate upper and lower O-ring with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="s26504.4.11.2">
            <title>Fuel Injector Assembly</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, verify hold down bolt retainer is in position when installing
                        injector hold down clamp assembly.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2650497" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD08/D08211.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Fuel injector hold down clamp assembly (2004 and 2005 cylinder head applications)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 X 45</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retainer</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Clamp alignment index</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f2650497.1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD08/D08212.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Fuel injector hold down clamp assembly (2006 cylinder head application)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Bolt, M8 X 45</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Retainer</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Clamp alignment index</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align injector assembly clamp alignment slot with hold down clamp alignment index. This
                    aligns the injector correctly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650498" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd11/d1107.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installation of injector</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector hold down clamp assembly</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install fuel injector assembly by lowering fuel injector and hold down clamp assembly as
                    one unit into injector bore.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f265498.1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD31/D31554.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Fuel Injector Hold Down Wrench</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f2650499" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD11/D1156.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Fuel Injector Hold Down Wrench installed</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel injector hold down clamp assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Injector Hold Down Wrench</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent damage to fuel injector assemblies, do not use air power tools to remove or install
                        injectors.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use the Fuel Injector Hold Down Wrench to install the fuel injector hold down clamp
                    assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten hold down clamp bolt to the special torque .</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650499.1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figD08/D08203.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installation of injector harness connector</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">O-ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Injector harness connector</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace O-ring on injector harness connector.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position connector (identification marks face up) and push connector straight into
                    mounting hole.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, be sure injector wiring is clear of moving parts.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
